Package ca.corefacility.bioinformatics.irida.model

Class PathConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.corefacility.bioinformatics.irida.model.PathConverter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.hibernate.usertype.UserType
    @MappedSuperclass
public class PathConverter
extends Object
implements org.hibernate.usertype.UserType
    Converts a Path to a String before persisting a value to a column in a database. Allows us to store a the absolute path to a file instead of trying to store the file in the relational database. This implementation makes me very sad. It's a bit of a hack:
    1. We're annotating the class with MappedSuperclass so that hibernate will look at it and say "Hey, I need to manage this."
    2. We're annotating the class with TypeDef so that we can tell hibernate: "use this class to convert a Path to some sort of database column."
    This is ugly because we're using Hibernate-specific implementations of stuff. Ideally, we'd use the @Converter stuff that comes with JPA2.1, but Hibernate Envers barfs when you use the JPA markdownConverter annotations. See: https://hibernate.atlassian.net/browse/HHH-9042 I e-mailed the author of the bug report because he mentioned that he had a workaround. If he gets back to me, I will create another merge request to remove this class and replace with with a much more sane JPA-compliant version.
